# Introduction
------
The goal of this plugin is to generate a html page where you can see the documentation method (name of method, input parameters, output parameters, etc) allowing you to call the methods and injecting an json input and receive a json output.

In the first phase you only can configure for one method and using primitive data type. We will have the following features in the following order:

1. HTML page with method documentation. :heavy_check_mark:
2. You can perform a request to one method. :soon:
3. You can perform a request to method with non primitive data types. :soon:
3. You can have a html page with multiple methods documentation and can perform a request for each one. :soon:

# How can you do magic?
------
You only need to add a txt file with the format bellow and copy the following profile for your pom.xml file.

Config file template:

```
<Title> - <A simple description>

@doclib
beanIdentification:  <The id of bean, you only need this if you set a configFilePathAppContext. E.g: com.sesame.helper.checkValue>
className: <The name of class. E.g: CheckValue>
packageName: <The package of class declared up side. E.g: com.sesame.helper>
methodName: <The method name. E.g: isValid>
methodDescription: <A simple description of method. E.g: Check if string is valid>
return: <The return type of method, following with a description using `-`. E.g: Boolean - the result of check>
param-1: <The type of first parameter, following with a description using `-`. E.g: String - The value>
param-2: <The type of second parameter, following with a description using `-`. E.g: String - The value>
...
@enddoclib
```

| Field                    | Description                                                             | Possible Values       | Mandatory          |
| -------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------|--------------------|
| phase                    | You can set with one of the following maven phases.                     | test, verify, install | *                  |
| goal                     | This is a goal for the plugin. Please don't change this value!          | testing               | *                  |
| configFilePath           | You need to set with the path where you put the documentation file.     |                       | *                  |
| configType               | You need to set with the type of file you create the documentation.     | TEXT, YAML            | default TEXT       |
| configFilePathAppContext | You can set this if you want to load dependency beans.                  |                       |                    |

```
        <profile>
            <id>execSesame</id>

            <build>
                <plugins>
                    <plugin>
                        <groupId>com.sesame.helper</groupId>
                        <artifactId>sesame-java-plugin</artifactId>
                        <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
                        <configuration>
						    <configFilePath>src/test/resources/config.txt</configFilePath>
                            <configType>TEXT</configType>
                            <configFilePathAppContext>src/test/resources/beans.xml</configFilePathAppContext>
                        </configuration>
                        <executions>
                            <execution>
                                <phase>compile</phase>
                                <goals>
                                    <goal>testing</goal>
                                </goals>
                            </execution>
                        </executions>
                    </plugin>
                </plugins>
            </build>
        </profile>
    </profiles>
```

